  "prompt": "What should be my individual subject scores in NEET 2017?",
  "response": "The NEET (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test) score requirements can vary depending on various factors, including the category you belong to (e.g., general, OBC, SC/ST) and the college or university you are aiming for. The cut-off scores can also change from year to year based on the difficulty of the exam, the number of candidates, and other factors.\n\nHowever, if you're looking for individual subject scores from NEET 2017, it's important to note that NEET is scored out of a total of 720 marks, with three subjects: Physics, Chemistry, and Biology (comprising Botany and Zoology). Each subject is scored out of 180 marks.\n\nIf you're aiming for a good overall score, your individual subject scores would ideally be balanced, but it's difficult to recommend exact scores without knowing how competitive your target colleges are. Generally, securing at least 50-60% in each subject is a good guideline to aim for.\n\nIf you have a specific target score in mind or if you're looking to reach a particular percentile, providing additional context can help in giving more tailored advice. Otherwise, you may want to check the official NEET 2017 cutoff scores released by the National Testing Agency (NTA) or the respective colleges for more specific guidance.",
